# .claspignore — controls which files get pushed to the Apps Script project.
# Pattern: glob-style (.gitignore-like). Lines beginning with "!" are NEGATIONS
# (files to INCLUDE despite a broader exclusion).
#
# Strategy: WHITELIST. Ignore everything by default; explicitly include only
# the two files Apps Script actually needs (manifest + main script). Prevents
# accidentally shipping Python tooling (generate_corrections.py, etc.), docs,
# build files, or .claude/ config to the production Apps Script project.
#
# Add new files here only if they belong in the Apps Script editor:
# - .gs / .js → Apps Script source files
# - .html    → HtmlService templates (we don't have any yet)
# - appsscript.json → manifest (already whitelisted)

# Default: ignore everything
**/*

# Whitelist: only push these to Apps Script
!appsscript.json
!Code.js
